To compile you need to setup C99FLAGS according to your compiler.

Examples:

gcc + bash:

 % CC=gcc C99FLAGS="-std=c99" make

This is a trick to turn off 'extended precision',
see: http://www.network-theory.co.uk/docs/gccintro/gccintro_70.html

== Useful additional packages ==

gnuplot (> 4.2)
graphiz
http://code.google.com/p/jrfonseca/wiki/Gprof2Dot
